# Components Guide

- All reusable UI components live in [`src/components/`](mdc:src/components).
- Atomic UI primitives (e.g., Button, Card, Table, Input, etc.) are in [`src/components/ui/`](mdc:src/components/ui).
- Compose higher-level components from these primitives for consistency and maintainability.
- Follow the pattern: keep logic minimal in UI primitives, and extend via composition in feature or page-level components.
- Use Tailwind CSS utility classes for styling, and prefer Shadcn UI/Radix UI patterns for accessibility and design.
- Example: To use a button, import from [`src/components/ui/button.tsx`](mdc:src/components/ui/button.tsx).
- For new UI primitives, add them to the `ui/` subdirectory and document usage inline.
